HEADWORD: Sanitation
<hw>San`i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
rendering sanitary; the science of sanitary conditions; the preservation
of health; the use of sanitary measures; hygiene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How much <qex>sanitation</qex> has advanced during the last half
century.</q> <rj><qau>H. Hartshorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanity</ent>⟦br⟧
